    <item>
      <title>Query results</title>
      <link>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/query-results/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/query-results/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;query-results&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#query-results&#34;&gt;&#xA;Query results&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Unlike AQL, the result of an FQL query is an not always array of values. The individual values can be returned, not wrapped by an array.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For example, when the &lt;code&gt;RETURN&lt;/code&gt; statement is used as the last query statement, a values gets returned as it is:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-380-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 90px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;RETURN 1&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-380-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-375-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 90px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;1&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-375-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-617-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 90px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;RETURN { foo: &#34;bar&#34; }&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-617-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-933-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 90px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;{ &#34;foo&#34;: &#34;bar&#34; }&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-933-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;However, when returning data from an iteration, the result values will be always an array:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Query errors</title>
      <link>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/query-errors/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/query-errors/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;query-errors&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#query-errors&#34;&gt;&#xA;Query errors&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;Issuing an invalid query to Ferret will result in a parse error if the query is syntactically invalid. The Ferret compiler will detect such errors during query inspection and abort further processing. Instead, an error message are returned so that the errors can be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Under some circumstances, executing a query may also produce run-time errors that cannot be predicted from inspecting the query text alone. This is because queries may use data from collections that may also be inhomogeneous. Some examples that will cause run-time errors are:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
